#. type: Title #
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:1
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:4
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Subaddress"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:7
#, markdown-text
msgid "Subaddress is what you should be using by default to receive Monero."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:8
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Learn for what you are being paid"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:11
#, markdown-text
msgid "By providing a unique subaddress for each anticipated payment you will know for what you are being paid."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:13
#, markdown-text
msgid "This use case overlaps with integrated addresses. Subaddresses are generally prefered for reasons outlined below."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:14
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Prevent payer from linking your payouts together"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:18
#, markdown-text
msgid "To prevent the payer from linking your payouts together simply generate a new subaddress for each payout.  This way specific service (like anonymous exchange) that sends you Monero won't (easilly) know it is you again receving Monero."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:20
#, markdown-text
msgid "The exception to this is when a service (or group of colluding services) decides to actively attack you, one address at the time, with the so-called [Janus attack](https://web.getmonero.org/2019/10/18/subaddress-janus.html), which risks them losing funds. If you need perfect unlinkability of your receivables, the only solution remains to use a separate seed (separate Monero wallet)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:22
#, markdown-text
msgid "Also, note it won't help if you have an account with the service. Then your payouts are already linked in the service database, regardless of Monero."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:23
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Group funds into accounts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:26
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**Accounts** are a convenience wallet-level feature to group subaddresses under one label and balance.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:28
#, markdown-text
msgid "You may want to organize your funds into accounts like \"cash\", \"work\", \"trading\", \"mining\", \"donations\", etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:30
#, markdown-text
msgid "As accounts are only groupings of subaddresses, they themselves do not have an address."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:32
#, markdown-text
msgid "Accounts are deterministically derived from the root private key along with subaddresses."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:34
#, markdown-text
msgid "Accounts are similar to subaccounts in your classic bank account. There is a very important difference though. In Monero funds don't really sit on accounts or public addresses. Public addresses are conceptually a gateway or a routing mechanism. Funds sit on transactions' unspent outputs. Thus, a single transaction can - in principle - aggregate and spend outputs from multiple addresses (and by extension from multiple accounts). The CLI or GUI wallet may not directly support creating such transactions for simplicity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:36
#, markdown-text
msgid "In short, think of accounts as a **soft** grouping of your funds."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:37
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Why not multiple wallets?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:41
#, markdown-text
msgid "The advantage over creating multiple wallets is that you only have a **single seed** to manage.  All subaddresses can be derived from the wallet seed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:43
#, markdown-text
msgid "Additionally, you conveniently manage your subaddresses within a single user interface."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:44
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Wallet level feature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:47
#, markdown-text
msgid "Subaddresses and accounts are a wallet-level feature to construct and interpret transactions. They do not affect the consensus."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:48
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Data structure"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:51
#, markdown-text
msgid "Subaddress has a dedicated \"network byte\":"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:55
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Index       | Size in bytes    | Description\n"
"------------|------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------\n"
"0           | 1                | identifies the network and address type; [42](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/31bdf7bd113c2576fe579ef3a25a2d8fef419ffc/src/cryptonote_config.h#L171) - mainnet; [36](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/31bdf7bd113c2576fe579ef3a25a2d8fef419ffc/src/cryptonote_config.h#L200) - stagenet; [63](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/31bdf7bd113c2576fe579ef3a25a2d8fef419ffc/src/cryptonote_config.h#L185) - testnet\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:57
#, markdown-text
msgid "Otherwise the data structure is the same as for the [standard address](/public-address/standard-address/#data-structure)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:58
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Generating"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:61
#, markdown-text
msgid "Each subaddress conceptually has:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:64
#, markdown-text
msgid "account index (also known as \"major\" index)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:64
#, markdown-text
msgid "subaddress index within the account (also known as \"minor\" index)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:66
#, markdown-text
msgid "The indexes are 0-based. By default wallets use account index 0."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:69
#, markdown-text
msgid "The indexes are not directly included in the subaddress data structure.  Instead, they are used as input to generating subaddress keys."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:70
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Private view key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:73
#, markdown-text
msgid "A per-subaddress scalar `m` is derived as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:75
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "    m = Hs(\"SubAddr\" || a || account_index || subaddress_index_within_account)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:77
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:94
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:106
#, markdown-text
msgid "Where:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
#, markdown-text
msgid "`Hs` is a Keccak-256 hash function interpreted as integer and modulo `l` (maximum edwards25519 scalar)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
#, markdown-text
msgid "`||` is a byte array concatenation operator"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
#, markdown-text
msgid "`SubAddr` is a 0-terminated fixed string (8 bytes total)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
#, markdown-text
msgid "`a` is a private view key of the standard address (a 32 byte little endian unsigned integer)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
#, markdown-text
msgid "`account_index` is index of an account (a 32 bit little endian unsigned integer)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:84
#, markdown-text
msgid "`subaddress_index_within_account` is index of the subaddress within the account (a 32 bit little endian unsigned integer)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/subaddress.md:86
#, markdown-text
msgid "Deriving \"sub view keys\" from the main view key allows for creating a view only wallet that monitors the entire wallet including subaddresses."
msgstr ""

